description: Data was loaded from TCGA DCC on July 2016 for Somatic Mutations MAF data.

fields.description: TCGA barcode identifier for the study participant, eg TCGA-02-0001
fields.name: ParticipantBarcode

fields.description: Original TCGA tumor sample barcode. TCGA-WC-A885-01A, TCGA-HQ-A2OF-01A.
fields.name: Tumor_SampleBarcode

fields.description: Original TCGA tumor aliquote barcode. Examples: TCGA-WC-A885-01A,TCGA-XF-AAN3-01A
fields.name: Tumor_AliquotBarcode

fields.description: Tumor Sample Type Code. The current subset of 5 values used are:TB, TM, TAP, TP, TR.See https://Gdc.Cancer.Gov/Resources-TCGA-Users/TCGA-Code-Tables/Sample-Type-Codes
fields.name: Tumor_SampleTypeLetterCode

fields.description: Sample Barcode For The Normal Tissue. Examples: TCGA-V4-A9EI-10A, TCGA-V4-A9EI-10A
fields.name: Normal_SampleBarcode

fields.description: Aliquot Barcode For The Normal Tissue. Examples: TCGA-CR-7385-10A-01D-2013-08, TCGA-DX-A3M1-10A-01D-A22A-09
fields.name: Normal_AliquotBarcode

fields.description: Sample Type Letter Code. The subset of 4 values currently used are: NBC, NB, NT, NBM. See https://Gdc.Cancer.Gov/Resources-TCGA-Users/TCGA-Code-Tables/Sample-Type-Codes
fields.name: Normal_SampleTypeLetterCode

fields.description: TCGA study abbreviation, eg LAML. Full list available at https://gdc.cancer.gov/resources-TCGA-users/TCGA-code-tables/TCGA-study-abbreviations
fields.name: Study

fields.description: Ensembl Annotation Transcript ID. Example: ENST00000542285.1
fields.name: Annotation_Transcript

fields.description: Integer value giving the total mutations in the gene. Examples: 1, 2, 57, 12, 61, 1189, 5
fields.name: CCLE_ONCOMAP_Total_Mutations_In_Gene

fields.description: Integer value giving the total alterations in the gene. Examples: 93, 196, 121, 8, 6, 45, 15
fields.name: COSMIC_Total_Alterations_In_Gene

fields.description: One or more genome sequencing center reporting the variant
fields.name: Center

fields.description: Chromosome, possible values: chr1-22, and chrX
fields.name: Chromosome

fields.description: DNA Repair Genes Role. Examples (from the 24 types used): Mismatch excision repair (MMR), Direct reversal of damage, Rad6 pathway, Chromatin Structure, Other BER factors, Repair of DNA-protein crosslinks
fields.name: DNARepairGenes_Role

fields.description: DbSNP reference SNP number, eg rs121913500 -- may be a list, or may be null. Examples: rs199875324, rs190442239|rs373000930,rs34463219|rs200326823|rs386737232|rs398046742
fields.name: DbSNP_RS

fields.description: DbSNP validation status. Either byFrequency or null.
fields.name: DbSNP_Val_Status

fields.description: Associated Drug Bank Names and IDs. Examples: Succinic acid(DB00139), Danazol(DB01406)|Gonadorelin(DB00644)|Nafarelin(DB00666). Note: this field is usually blank.
fields.name: DrugBank

fields.description: Highest numeric genomic position of the reported variant on the genomic reference sequence. Mutation end coordinate
fields.name: End_Position

fields.description: Entrez gene ID (an integer). 0 is used for regions that do not correspond to a gene region or Ensembl ID
fields.name: Entrez_Gene_Id

fields.description: Percent GC content. Examples:0.353, 0.527, 0.617
fields.name: GC_Content

fields.description: Transcript name from GENCODE Examples: ADC-002, HCP5-001
fields.name: GENCODE_Transcript_Name

fields.description: Transcript status from GENCODE. Either KNOWN, PUTATIVE, NOVEL (also can be blank)
fields.name: GENCODE_Transcript_Status

fields.description: Transcript type From GENCODE. Examples (from 23 types used):miRNA, rRNA, snRNA, TR_D_gene, protein_coding, misc_RNA. For more info: https://www.gencodegenes.org/pages/biotypes.html
fields.name: GENCODE_Transcript_Type

fields.description: GO Biological Process. Example: morphogenesis of an epithelial sheet (GO:0002011)|regulation of small GTPase mediated signal transduction (GO:0051056)|small GTPase mediated signal transduction (GO:0007264). For More Information: http://geneontology.org/docs/ontology-documentation/
fields.name: GO_Biological_Process

fields.description: GO Cellular Component. Examples: extracellular space (GO:0005615), basement membrane (GO:0005604)For More Information: http://geneontology.org/docs/ontology-documentation/
fields.name: GO_Cellular_Component

fields.description: GO Molecular Function.Example: carbohydrate binding (GO:0030246)|identical protein binding (GO:0042802).For More Information: http://geneontology.org/docs/ontology-documentation/
fields.name: GO_Molecular_Function

fields.description: Gene Type. Examples (from 22 types used): linkRNA, miRNA, rRNA, protein_coding, pseudogene, antisense.
fields.name: Gene_Type

fields.description: Genome location and base change. Examples: g.chr17:27530935G>A,g.chr21:26020893_26020896delTTCC
fields.name: Genome_Change

fields.description: HGNC accession numbers.Examples:AF134415, M12272. See https://www.genenames.org/help/search/
fields.name: HGNC_Accession_Numbers

fields.description: HGNC CCDS IDs. Examples: CCDS19.2, CCDS50.1.See https://www.genenames.org/help/search/,https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/projects/CCDS/CcdsBrowse.cgi
fields.name: HGNC_CCDS_IDs

fields.description: Ensembl ID. Example: ENSG00000159403.See https://useast.ensembl.org/info/genome/stable_ids/index.html
fields.name: HGNC_Ensembl_ID_Supplied_By_Ensembl

fields.description: HGNC ID. A unique ID provided by the HGNC for each gene with an approved symbol. HGNC IDs remain stable even if a name or symbol changes. Examples: 37190, 18046, 79, 212
fields.name: HGNC_HGNC_ID

fields.description: HGNC locus group. The word <locus> is not a synonym for gene but refers to a map position. Four locus group types are used here: protein-coding gene, non-coding RNA, other, pseudogene.
fields.name: HGNC_Locus_Group

fields.description: HGNC locus type. The word <locus> is not a synonym for gene but refers to a map position. 19 locustypes are used here. Examples: RNA, Y; T cell receptor gene;gene with protein product; pseudogene
fields.name: HGNC_Locus_Type

fields.description: OMIM ID. Examples: 608580, 611916.Online Mendelian Inheritance in Man (OMIM) is a continuously updated catalog of human genes and genetic disorders and traits, with a particular focus on the gene-phenotype relationship.
fields.name: HGNC_OMIM_ID_Supplied_By_NCBI

fields.description: RefSeq protein-coding or non-coding transcript ID.Examples:NM_001733, NR_040662, XM_006724392.https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RefSeq, https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK21091/table/ch18.T.refseq_accession_numbers_and_mole/?report=objectonly
fields.name: HGNC_RefSeq_Supplied_By_NCBI

fields.description: UCSC gene ID. Examples:uc011aic,uc002xul.4
fields.name: HGNC_UCSC_ID_Supplied_By_UCSC

fields.description: UniProt ID. Examples: A2VEC9, Q7RTT6. See https://www.uniprot.org/help/accession_numbers
fields.name: HGNC_UniProt_ID_Supplied_By_UniProt

fields.description: HUGO symbol for the gene (HUGO symbols are always in all caps). Unknown is used for regions that do not correspond to a gene
fields.name: Hugo_Symbol

fields.description: An assessment of the mutation as somatic, germline, LOH, post transcriptional modification, unknown, or none. The values allowed in this field are constrained by the value in the Validation_Status field
fields.name: Mutation_Status

fields.description: The reference genome used for the alignment (GRCh37)
fields.name: NCBI_Build

fields.description: Primary Data Genotype. Matched Normal Sequencing Allele 1. A - Symbol For A Deletion Represents A Variant. A - Symbol For An Insertion Represents Wild-Type Allele. Novel Inserted Sequence For Insertion Does Not Include Flanking Reference Bases (Cleared In Somatic Maf).Examples:C,GAA, TTTC, GCCGGAGAGGAG, TATGA
fields.name: Normal_Seq_Allele1

fields.description: Matched Normal Sequencing Allele 2. Examples:GCGGAGAGGAG, C, ACC, TCT, TTTC
fields.name: Normal_Seq_Allele2

fields.description: Secondary Data From Orthogonal Technology. Matched Normal Genotyping (Validation) For Allele 1. A - Symbol For A Deletion Represents A Variant. A - Symbol For An Insertion Represents Wild-Type Allele. Novel Inserted Sequence For Insertion Does Not Include Flanking Reference Bases (Cleared In Somatic Maf). Examples:GGG, AAA, TGCCGGCCT, GG
fields.name: Normal_Validation_Allele1

fields.description: Secondary Data From Orthogonal Technology. Matched Normal Genotyping (Validation) For Allele 2 (Cleared In Somatic Maf). Examples: GCCGGAGAGGAG, AAG, GT, GTAA
fields.name: Normal_Validation_Allele2

fields.description: Open Regulatory Annotation Database Id. Example: OREG0026204, OREG0023259
fields.name: OREGANNO_ID

fields.description: Changes An Amino Acid To Another Amino Acid. Examples: p.G464V, p.N3185S,p.K1061fs
fields.name: Protein_Change

fields.description: Reference allele Per VCF Specs, And Its Five Flanking Base Pairs. Examples: GTAGGAAGCAGCCAGCAAAAG, TGGTTCTACCTTCACAATCCA
fields.name: Ref_Context

fields.description: The plus strand reference allele at this position. Includes the deleted sequence for a deletion or - for an insertion
fields.name: Reference_Allele

fields.description: RefSeq protein ID. Examples:NP_078970.3, NP_057064.1. Seehttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RefSeq, https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK21091/table/ch18.T.refseq_accession_numbers_and_mole/?report=objectonly
fields.name: Refseq_Prot_Id

fields.description: Secondary variant classification. Example (from the 9 descriptions currently used): In_Frame_Del,Intron, Nonsense_Mutation, Silent, Frame_Shift_Del, Frame_Shift_Ins, Missense_Mutation
fields.name: Secondary_Variant_Classification

fields.description: Molecular assay type used to produce the analytes used for sequencing. Allowed values are a subset of the SRA 1.5 library_strategy field values. This subset matches those used at CGHub. Allowed values: RNA-Seq, WXS, Other, Capture
fields.name: Sequence_Source

fields.description: Instrument used to produce primary sequence data
fields.name: Sequencer

fields.description: Lowest numeric position of the reported variant on the genomic reference sequence. Mutation start coordinate
fields.name: Start_Position

fields.description: SwissProtaccession ID. Examples: Q15835, P59797.See https://www.uniprot.org/help/accession_numbers
fields.name: SwissProt_Acc_Id

fields.description: Swissprot entry ID. Examples: AZIN2_HUMAN, NIM1_HUMAN
fields.name: SwissProt_Entry_Id

fields.description: Transcript exon. An integer value. Examples: 2, 22, 1, 7, 16, 54
fields.name: Transcript_Exon

fields.description: Transcript position.An integer value: Examples: 110, 1047, 401, 6568.
fields.name: Transcript_Position

fields.description: Transcript strand. Either + or - (or blank)
fields.name: Transcript_Strand

fields.description: Primary data genotype for tumor sequencing (discovery) allele 1. A - symbol for a deletion represents a variant. A - symbol for an insertion represents wild-type allele. Novel inserted sequence for insertion does not include flanking reference bases
fields.name: Tumor_Seq_Allele1

fields.description: Primary data genotype for tumor sequencing (discovery) allele 2. A - symbol for a deletion represents a variant. A - symbol for an insertion represents wild-type allele. Novel inserted sequence for insertion does not include flanking reference bases
fields.name: Tumor_Seq_Allele2

fields.description: Secondary data from orthogonal technology. Tumor genotyping (validation) for allele 1. A - symbol for a deletion represents a variant. A - symbol for an insertion represents wild-type allele. Novel inserted sequence for insertion does not include flanking reference bases
fields.name: Tumor_Validation_Allele1

fields.description: Secondary data from orthogonal technology. Tumor genotyping (validation) for allele 2
fields.name: Tumor_Validation_Allele2

fields.description: UniProt AA position. An integer value. Examples: 384, 3881, 312, 694
fields.name: UniProt_AApos

fields.description: UnitProt Region. Examples: Cadherin 5. {ECO:0000255|PROSITE- ProRule:PRU00043},EGF-like 1. {ECO:0000255|PROSITE- ProRule:PRU00076}
fields.name: UniProt_Region

fields.description: The assay platforms used for the validation call
fields.name: Validation_Method

fields.description: Translational effect of variant allele
fields.name: Variant_Classification

fields.description: Type of mutation. TNP (tri-nucleotide polymorphism) is analogous to DNP (di-nucleotide polymorphism) but for three consecutive nucleotides. ONP (oligo-nucleotide polymorphism) is analogous to TNP but for consecutive runs of four or more (SNP, DNP, TNP, ONP, INS, DEL, or Consolidated)
fields.name: Variant_Type

fields.description: CDNA change. Examples: c.3236G>A,c.143_147delCTGCC, c.4417_4418insCAA
fields.name: cDNA_Change
